value.0: Gunnar is a warrior in his fifties, having served as Isviks protector for most of his life. The few bandits that have haunted the isles roads here and there always made sure to stay well clear of him and his axe. Those who did not, did not get second chances.

Stories speak of a poor traveller, victim to a snowstorm one winter night. In the midst of frostbite and unconsciousness, he stumbled upon an isolated monastery, dedicated to Ilmater. The monks took him in, gave him shelter, food and most notably, a pair of thick, snow-wading boots.

With new-found vigor, he left the next day, boots firmly clad. Winter gave way to spring, and spring gave way to further winters, until the man was wealthy enough to return to that secluded monastery, to give his thanks for supporting him at his time of need.

To his surprise, he could not find the monastery, no matter how hard he searched the land. The blizzard returned once more during his searches, covering the land in a white blanket. One quiet night resting in his makeshift shelter, he found a dying man, frozen half to death. After feeding him and nursing him to health, he gifted the man those same boots he received years prior, and decided to build a small monastery in place of the one he could no longer find.
This cloak protects against the piercing cold in Firth and against Cold Magic in general.
This is Gunnars greataxe, an old family relic. Its heavy but an utterly deadly weapon in the right hands.
